    <paperBody>
        <page n="01" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.08.07.01">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Horrors of War</head>
                <origin>Cincinnati Commercial</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Article from a correspondent at the Battle of Rich Mountain and at Bull
                    Run.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>How the Troops are Paid</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Lists the salaries of Northern military officers.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>The Rebel Prisoners</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reports on the rebel prisoners landed at Fort Lafayette.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>Soldiers' Letters</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Explains that soldiers' letters will now be sent free of charge.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Various battlefield reports, including some from Southern papers.</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.08.07.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Democratic County Meeting</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Announces that the Franklin County Democrats will meet at the Court House
                    on August 13th to prepare for the next election.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>County Meeting</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Encourages Democrats to attend the August 13th meeting and to stand fast by
                    the principles of the Democratic party.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Discontinued</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Spirit explains that it will cease the semi-weekly edition and return
                    to a weekly.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Contemptible</head>
                <origin>Harrisburg Patriot and Union</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Denies a rumor, reported in the Harrisburg Telegraph, that Captains
                    received gold and silver to pay their troops, but sold the specie and paid the
                    men in bank notes.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Patriots and Traitors</head>
                <origin>Harrisburg Patriot and Union</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"In good old times...a patriot...might support the Administration in Power
                    or oppose it, without having his loyalty to the Government or his patriotism
                    questioned."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Alleges that any condemnation of the Republican administration leads to
                    accusations of treason and want of patriotism.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>True Patriotism</head>
                <origin>Presbyterian</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Asserts that those self-styled patriots who fight the war only with their
                    tongues or pens should tone down their fervor for the war.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>Army Officers too Conspicuous in Action</head>
                <origin>Philadelphia Inquirer</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Suggests that officers go into battle in less distinctive uniforms as they
                    make easy targets.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>Troops Furnished by Pennsylvania</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Lists the number of troops furnished by Pennsylvania.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Various military reports.</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="03" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.08.07.03">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Camp Meeting</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript>
                    <p>The <emph rend="italic">"Union Camp Meeting"</emph> of the Churches of God in
                        Chambersburg, Fayetteville, Orrstown, Shippensburg, Newburg, &amp;c.,
                        will be held on the old ground, one mile from Scotland station; and will
                        commence D.V. on Thursday, the 15th of August.</p>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Announces that "Union Camp Meeting" of the Churches of God will be held on
                    August 15.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="o">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Died</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Myers</ln>
                        <fn>Julian</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Died on July 29 at age 3 years.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Advertisements and markets</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="04" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.08.07.04">
